Serve these files exactly as they are.

GitHub Pages runs Jekyll over a repo by default, which processes files on their way out.
A card is a single self-contained HTML file whose payload is base64 ciphertext — there is
nothing here to templatise, and anything that rewrites a byte of it breaks decryption
(GCM authenticates: one changed byte and the card won't open at all). This file turns
Jekyll off.
